Triage Staffing
Senior Software Engineer, Elixir
RemoteUnited StatesTechnologyFull time

OVERVIEW
APPLICATION
Description
Triage, an award-winning and top-ranked medical staffing agency experiencing unprecedented growth, is seeking a highly skilled and experienced Senior Software Engineer. Headquartered in Omaha, NE, with an additional office in Loveland, OH, Triage is at the forefront of the healthcare industry, connecting thousands of traveling healthcare providers with facilities across all 50 states.

This role is remote.

Requirements
Software Development: Design, code, test, and maintain software applications using Elixir, Phoenix, and LiveView.
Database Management: Develop and optimize PostgreSQL database schemas, queries, and performance.
Architecture and Design: Collaborate with cross-functional teams to architect scalable and maintainable software solutions.
Code Reviews: Review code and provide constructive feedback to fellow engineers, fostering a culture of quality and continuous improvement.
Paired Programming: Work closely with other engineers to solve complex problems.
Decompose Requirements: Work with product teams to decompose feature requirements into easily communicated development items.
Performance Optimization: Identify and address performance bottlenecks, ensuring our applications are highly responsive and efficient.
A Commitment to Testing: Write unit and integration tests, and participate in review processes to ensure software reliability.
Security: Implement and adhere to best practices for application security, data protection, and user authentication.
Version Control: Use Git for version control, branching, and merging code changes effectively.
Collaboration: Work closely with product managers, designers, and other engineers to deliver high-quality software products.
Qualifications

Proven experience as a Senior Software Engineer or similar role, with a strong track record of delivering complex software projects. A demonstrable established body of work is preferable.
Proficiency in Elixir and the Phoenix framework
Experience with LiveView and real-time web applications
Strong knowledge of PostgreSQL, including database design and optimization
Proficiency in HTML, CSS, and JavaScript
Familiarity with front-end technologies and frameworks is a plus
Excellent communication and collaboration skills
Experience with Agile development methodologies
Benefits
Salary: $150,000 - $160,000
Medical, dental, and vision insurance
401k with company match
Flexible Time Off policy + Paid Holidays
Staff events, on-site & remote
Employee Assistance Program
